Mr. Peter Ifeanyi Eleberi, a member of the Newspapers/ Magazines Distribution Association of Nigeria (NDAN, who died at the age of 64, will be buried on Thursday in his compound in from Uzir Aumu Autonomous Community, Mgbidi, Imo State, Oru West Local Government, Imo State. A statement signed by Mr. Godwin Akpan, the chairman of the Lagos State chapter of the association, said that a wake-keep will take place on Wednesday at his compound before a funeral service and interment service will take place on April 21 2022. The chairman said that the deceased was a former public relations officer of the association and described him as an active member of the group.